Description: MPRIS2 bridge for Snapcast clients
 snapcastmpris exposes the local Snapcast client (snapclient) on D-Bus as
 an MPRIS2 MediaPlayer2, allowing standard media controls (play / pause
 / stop) and Snapserver stream switching from any MPRIS2-aware client.
 .
 By default the bridge registers on the system bus (matching upstream
 hifiberry behaviour); this can be switched to the session bus via the
 dbus-bus key. The configuration is read from
 $XDG_CONFIG_HOME/snapcastmpris/snapcastmpris.conf with a fallback to
 /etc/snapcastmpris.conf. An example configuration is shipped at
 /usr/share/snapcastmpris/snapcastmpris.conf.
 .
 Both a system systemd unit (default, system bus) and a user unit
 (for per-user / session-bus deployments) are shipped; neither is
 auto-enabled.
